title: One dead in Bacchus Marsh crash
text:
Two die as cars exit Victorian roads - Yahoo7 Two men have died on Victoria's roads early on Saturday morning. 
One man, believed to be in his 20s is dead and another is in hospital after their car left the road and slammed into a tree near Bacchus Marsh. 
The driver of the car appeared to lose control and hit the tree in the incident which occurred in the early hours of Saturday morning. 
Then a few hours later a lone driver, also believed to be in his 20s, left the road and crashed into a tree at Newhaven, on Phillip Island.
